tion in 1949 may think of him as a prophet of village simplicity and the father of civil disobedience. Some may question or be confused by his teachings about economic and sexual matters, but most interpretations would agree that the Indian leader was an extraordinary person and public figure whose impact is still felt and will be felt for decades to come in many parts of the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Political.2bisacsh1 aEmbree, Ainslie T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoeber Rudolph, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKumar Bose, Nirmal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLevi, Werner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParel, Anthony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPotter, Karl H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPower, Paul F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPower, Paul F., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRam Nanda, Bal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmith, Donald E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStuart Nelson, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHawaii eBook Package Archive pre 2000z978311056415040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780824885342423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780824885342.jpg  a978-3-11-056415-0  Hawaii eBook Package Archive pre 2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter